Rating: 4
A wonderful and versatile dressing/sauce that can be modified in any number of ways for a variety of purposes. Last night I made it using half mayo and half plain yogurt to which I added the following: 1 T minced fresh tarragon, 1/4 cup finely diced mango, 1/2 pureed mango. I also followed the suggestion of another reviewer and used canned chipotle in adobo sauce. My family loved this on grilled shrimp and asparagus. This will be a regular part of the repertoire around here and I plan to make it with other additions as well...some ideas: peaches, mint, molasses, kalamata olives, cilantro, parsley, tomatoes (sundried or fresh), asiago, roasted corn...not all at once, of course, but I'll be trying all of them.

Rating: 4
