For a much more intense, spicer/smokier flavor, use canned chipotle pepper (in adobo sauce). Just mince one pepper (or more if you're brave) instead of using the powdered or chipotle hot sauce. Also, I second Phyl124's suggestion for fat-free mayo. With all the flavor from the chipotle, you won't miss the fat (and neither will your heart).

